<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The end-user UIs don&#x27;t ask you to calculate anything. Typically they have a slider from 100% to, say, 400% and let you set this to something like 145%.<p>This may take some getting used to if you&#x27;re familiar with DPI and already know the value you like, but for non-technical users it&#x27;s more approachable. Not everyone knows DPI or how many dots they want to their inches.<p>That the 145% is 1.45 under the hood is really an implementation detail.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371804&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369646%2344371804" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
